description:
A Utility-Scale Solar Design Engineer is evaluating land area constraints for a new solar plant in Phoenix, Arizona. Quantify the energy yield tradeoff of enabling tracker backtracking at Ground Coverage Ratios (GCRs) of 0.3, 0.4, and 0.5 using PySAM's Pvsamv1 module. Load the "FlatPlatePVSingleOwner" default configuration and use a Phoenix TMY weather file from SAM's bundled solar_resource directory. The simulation should use 1-axis tracking (subarray1_track_mode = 1) at 0 tilt (subarray1_tilt = 0) with default system capacity. For each GCR value (subarray1_gcr), determine the annual energy production both with backtracking (subarray1_backtrack = 1) and without (subarray1_backtrack = 0), calculating the percentage gain for each. Save the results to /home/ga/Documents/SAM_Projects/backtracking_impact.json using the following structure:

{
  "location_description": "Phoenix, AZ",
  "weather_file_used": "<filename>",
  "system_capacity_kw": <number>,
  "results": [
    {
      "gcr": 0.3,
      "annual_energy_no_backtrack_kwh": <number>,
      "annual_energy_with_backtrack_kwh": <number>,
      "backtrack_gain_percent": <number>
    },
    ...
  ]
}
